
'''= The project Open Micro-Metha is micro-methanization project that takes place into the community laboratory for citizen research open at la M[Y]ne, an ecohacklab in Lyon (France).''' 

More info via http://community.oscedays.org/t/challenge-open-micro-methanization/42


=Description=

"We aim at developing an innovative production, open source and "low-tech", and association services to enable the transformation of domestic organic waste into biogas in households, a building or a suburb. We seek to take action on the whole domestic organic waste cycle. The goal is to enable energy recovery through the production of biogas and to take care of the end of life after transformation - residus and digestate - through the setting up of closed circuit networks"

